Python: Return true if the two given integer values are equal or their sum or difference is 5

n = int(input("Enter the value"))
n1 = int(input("Enter the value"))
if n == n1 or n + n1 == 5 or n - n1 == 5:
    print ("True")
else:
    print ("False")



